<hl>
<seg id=1> August Retail Index 8.3 Percent Lower Than Last Year </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> The retail index for August has fallen 8.3 percent from that of last year. It is the twelfth month in a row that the index has fallen. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Since September 1997, the retail index has been compared to that of the same month of the previous year, and it has always fallen, showing that the retail industry here is struggling at a low tide. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> In comparison with July of this year, the retail index has fallen 8.3 percent. </seg>
<seg id=5> If one doesn't include automotive sales, the index has fallen 3.9 percent. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The numbers put out by the Bureau of Statistics show that almost all retail activity in August has been extremely slack. </seg>
<seg id=7> The value of July's car sales rose 41.4 percent, but in August they fell 19.9 percent. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Other businesses in the retail industry that have experienced decreases include furniture and appliances (8 percent), textiles and individual articles (7.8 percent), department stores and supermarkets(2.6 percent), gas stations (1.3 percent), and general stores (0.3 percent). </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> In other industries, the food and beverage index for August is down 4.5 percent in comparison to the same period for last year. This is the seventh month since February of 1998 that the index has fallen. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Nevertheless, when compared with July, the index for the industry has risen slightly by 1.4. percent. </seg>
<seg id=11> Consumer spending on food and beverages has increased from 245 million yuan in July to 248 million yuan. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> The increase is mainly due to the fast food industry's increase in value of 6.6 percent. </seg>
<seg id=13> Restaurants outside of the fast food industry also saw a business increase of 2.5 percent. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=14> Figures for the retail index and food and beverage industry index are released every month by the Bureau of Statistics to show the short-term performance of the two industries. </seg>
</p>
